            Senior Management and Directors Click on a person's name or image to view his or her biography. Click on a person's name to view his or her biography.Senior ManagementDawn M. ZierPresident and Chief Executive OfficerDawn Zier is the President and Chief Executive Officer of Nutrisystem, Inc. Ms. Zier joined Nutrisystem in November 2012 and oversees all aspects of Nutrisystem operations, including strategic partnerships, new product development, marketing and retail expansion. Since taking the helm, Dawn has led the turnaround of Nutrisystem by successfully changing the trajectory of the business and delivering customer and shareholder value with nine consecutive quarters of year-over-year growth. An engineer by education, Ms. Zier has spent most of her career in marketing, keeping her finger on the pulse of global consumers.

Ms. Zier came to Nutrisystem from Reader’s Digest Association (RDA), a leading global, multi-brand and multi-platform media and direct marketing company. A 20-year veteran of that organization, Ms. Zier served in a range of leadership positions, most recently as president of the company’s international business, with responsibility for $750 million of revenue and a team of 1,000 employees across Europe, Asia Pacific and Latin America.

Ms. Zier has over 20 years of senior-level accomplishments across both US and international operations accompanied by a strong and consistent track record of delivering results and driving efficiencies. She has significant expertise leading domestic and international marketing-driven organizations and in turning around and restructuring businesses. Ms. Zier has managed all parts of an integrated marketing organization, including direct-to-consumer, digital, database/analytics, retail, and brand positioning, and has product-based experience across both the food and health affinities.

In addition to being a member of Nutrisystem’s Board of Directors, Ms. Zier currently serves on the boards of Spirit Airlines and Velo Holdings, and was most recently elected as a member of C200, an invitation-only organization of the world’s most successful women corporate innovators and entrepreneurs. She previously served on the board of the Direct Marketing Association (DMA), the leading industry trade association, where she was a voting director from 2008 to 2015 and served as an Officer. She was a Board Trustee for the Direct Marketing Educational Foundation from 2010 to 2012. From 2005 to 2009, Ms. Zier chaired the Audit Bureau of Circulation (ABC) Magazine Directors’ Advisory Committee and was an active member of the Association of Magazine Media’s (MPA) Marketing Committee. Before joining RDA, Ms. Zier held positions at AT&T, Chase Manhattan Bank, and Prodigy Services Corporation. She has an MBA from the MIT Sloan School of Management as well as a Master’s of Science degree in Electrical Engineering and Computer Science from MIT. She received her Bachelor’s of Engineering degree in Electrical Engineering and Computer Science from the State University of New York at Stony Brook.Ralph J. MauroSenior Vice President, General Counsel and SecretaryRalph Mauro is Senior Vice President, General Counsel & Secretary of Nutrisystem, joining the company in June 2010.  From 1997 to June 2010, Mr. Mauro was a Partner with Kleinbard Bell & Brecker LLP, a Philadelphia corporate boutique law firm, where he represented many businesses in a variety of matters, including private equity and senior debt financing, joint ventures and strategic alliances, contract negotiation and documentation, and mergers and acquisitions. From September 1990 to December 1996, Mr. Mauro was an associate in the Business Departments of Kleinbard Bell & Brecker, Dechert LLP and Montgomery McCracken Walker & Rhoads LLP. 

Mr. Mauro received his law degree magna cum laude in 1990 from Villanova University School of Law, where he served as Editor-in-Chief of the Villanova Law Review. Prior to attending law school, Mr. Mauro practiced as a CPA at Arthur Andersen LLP. He received his undergraduate degree maxima cum laude from La Salle University in 1984. Mr. Mauro is admitted to the Bars of Pennsylvania and New Jersey.  Mr. Mauro also serves on the Boards of La Salle University, the Juvenile Diabetes Research Foundation (Eastern PA/DE Chapter), and Huntingdon Valley Country Club.Keira KrauszChief Marketing OfficerKeira Krausz is Executive Vice President and Chief Marketing Officer.  Ms. Krausz joined Nutrisystem in February 2013 and leads Nutrisystem’s marketing and communications functions. 
 
A 25-year marketing veteran with extensive experience across a variety of direct marketing channels, Ms. Krausz is a proven marketing leader with a track record of building profitable businesses, executing effective turnaround strategies, and identifying and monetizing new revenue streams in the direct consumer response sector.  From 2005 to 2012, Ms. Krausz served as Vice President of Marketing for QSP, Inc., a subsidiary of Time Inc. and the largest youth fundraising company in America.  During her tenure at QSP, she led the growth in e-commerce from nothing to over 25% of revenues, revamped the catalog and direct mail channels, developed social media strategies to drive customer engagement and sales, and ultimately worked with senior leadership to execute on the sale of the company in 2012.  Following the sale, she became head of new business development for Animated Storyboards, the largest global independent provider of television test spots to the advertising industry.

Prior to her tenure at Time Inc., Ms. Krausz was at Reader’s Digest Association (RDA) where she held a number of progressively-responsible positions in product management, marketing and business management, ultimately ascending to Vice President, General Manager of RDA’s Books & Music Business.  As the General Manager and Vice President of Marketing for Reader’s Digest’s Books & Music Direct Marketing, Ms. Krausz took the business from losing money to profitability by quickly assembling top talent, revitalizing product, developing new channels, and building a new book business in the health affinity that leveraged the company’s database.  

Ms. Krausz has an MBA from the Amos Tuck School of Business at Dartmouth College, and did her undergraduate work at the College of Arts and Sciences at Cornell University.Michael P. MonahanChief Financial OfficerMichael Monahan is Executive Vice President Administration and Chief Financial Officer.  Mr. Monahan joined Nutrisystem in May 2013.
  
Prior to his current role, Mr. Monahan served as Chief Financial Officer of PetroChoice Holdings, Inc., a privately-held distributor of industrial, commercial, and automotive lubricants. During his tenure, he was a member of the management team that grew the company organically and completed nine acquisitions that increased value for the shareholders. His appointment as Nutrisystem’s CFO represents a return to the company for Mr. Monahan, who served as Vice President of Finance from 2006 to 2009. Prior to this he served in financial roles at Exelon Corporation, Accenture and Arthur Andersen LLP.
 
Mr. Monahan earned an M.B.A. from the University of Chicago’s Booth School of Business and a B.A. from Villanova University.Board of DirectorsMichael J. HaganChairman of the BoardMr. Hagan has served as non-executive Chairman of the Board since April 2012.  He recently served as Lead Director of the Board of Directors from February 2012 until his appointment as Chairman.  Mr. Hagan is co-founder and Managing Partner of Hawk Capital Partners. Hawk Capital Partners, founded in December 2014, is a private equity firm focused on lower middle market businesses.  Prior to that, Mr. Hagan served as President and CEO of Lifeshield, Inc. from December 2009 until May 2014.  Lifeshield was acquired by DirecTV in June 2013. Prior to joining LifeShield, Mr. Hagan served as Chairman of the Board of Nutrisystem, Inc. from December 2002 to November 2008 and as CEO from December 2002 to May 2008.
 
Previously, Mr. Hagan co-founded Verticalnet, Inc. in 1995, a technology firm that provides supply management software and also created and managed industry specific “vertical” marketplaces. He served in a wide variety of roles at Verticalnet, including COO, CEO, and Chairman of the Board.
 
Prior to founding Verticalnet, Mr. Hagan served as a Vice President and Senior Manager at Merrill Lynch Asset Management from 1990 to 1995. He currently serves as a Director at Internet Capital Group, Inc.; Franklin Square Investment Corp. (FSIC); and Greater Philadelphia YMCA. 
 
Mr. Hagan has served as a member of the board of trustees of Saint Joseph’s University and various other private and public companies. He received a BS from St. Joseph’s University and was formerly a Certified Public Accountant.Robert F. BernstockMr. Bernstock has served as a Director since December 2005. He is currently self-employed as an independent consultant. 
 
Mr. Bernstock was named president of the Mailing and Shipping Services division of the United States Postal Service in June 2008 and served until June 2010. The division that he led produced more than $70 billion in annual revenue.  
Mr. Bernstock served as Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of SecureSheet Technologies, LLC from October 2006 through May 2008. Prior to that, he served as President and Chief Operating Officer of Scotts Miracle-Gro Company from October 2005 through September 2006. Mr. Bernstock was President of North America for The Scotts Miracle-Gro Company from May 2003 to September 2005. From October 2002 to April 2003, Mr. Bernstock was Senior Vice President and General Manager of The Dial Corporation. Earlier in his career, he was the President of the North American and International Divisions of Campbell Soup Company and was President, Chief Executive Officer and a director of both Vlasic Foods International and Atlas Commerce Inc. Mr. Bernstock is also a director of The Pantry, Inc. and a number of other private companies.Paul GuyardoMr. Guyardo has served as a Director since June 2012. Currently, Mr. Guyardo is the Chief Commercial Officer for Discovery Communications, the world’s #1 pay-TV programmer reaching nearly 3 billion cumulative subscribers in more than 220 countries and territories. In this role, he oversees U.S. ad sales, digital media, licensing and consumer products, consumer insights and data analytics.

Prior to Discovery Communications, Mr. Guyardo served most recently as Executive Vice President, Chief Revenue and Marketing Officer for DIRECTV, holding various positions from 2005 to 2015. In this role, he was responsible for all functions that drove the company’s $22 billion in U.S. Revenue including sales and distribution, marketing, product management, advertising, public relations, customer retention, the sports & entertainment businesses, pricing & packaging, consumer research, business analytics and ad sales. Under his leadership, DIRECTV’s subscriber base grew from 15.1 million in 2005 to nearly 20 million and revenue increased from $12 billion to $22 billion. Initiatives that he launched include reducing churn to the lowest level in the industry, rebranding DIRECTV as a premium brand in the pay-television category, growing direct sales from 25 percent to 50 percent of total enterprise sales, transforming directv.com into a major sales channel of highly profitable customers and a destination for more than 50 million self-care and entertainment transactions each year, rebuilding a network of more than 2,000 authorized dealers, substantially growing the Commercial business and brokering a national, multi-year agreement that enabled AT&T to sell DIRECTV to its customers as part of a bundle of telecommunication services. 

Prior to joining DIRECTV, Mr. Guyardo was Senior Vice President and Chief Marketing Officer for Kmart Corporation. He joined Kmart following the retail giant’s emergence from bankruptcy and was part of the senior management team that quickly returned the mass retailer to sales growth and profitability within 12 months. 

Before Kmart, Mr. Guyardo was Executive Vice President of Television and Marketing for HSN (formerly Home Shopping Network), an operating business unit of Barry Diller’s IAC/InterActiveCorp. During his tenure, HSN experienced eight consecutive years of sales and profit growth. 

He began his career in advertising and brand management, holding positions at AT&T, Johnson & Johnson, Saatchi & Saatchi and Tracy Locke/BBDO. 

Mr. Guyardo is the recipient of the 2010 Brand Builders Award (awarded by Broadcasting & Cable, Multichannel News and Promax/BDA), sits on the Board of Directors for Living Social, serves on the National Advisory Council for Northwestern University and is an executive mentor for the New York and New Jersey All-Stars Project. 

Mr. Guyardo holds bachelor’s and master’s degrees from Northwestern University.Jay HerrattiMr. Herratti has served as a Director since April 2013.  He currently serves as the Executive Director of TEDx, a global event and digital media platform formed to discover 'ideas worth spreading” and supported by the private non-profit Sapling Foundation. He also serves on the Board of Directors at Constant Contact, which helps more than half a million small organizations connect with their customers through a suite of online engagement marketing tools. Mr. Herratti is also the Principal of Jay Herratti Ventures where he is an investor and advisor to early-stage ventures.   
Mr. Herratti is an experienced strategic leader and digital expert with extensive experience in managing consumer, b2b, and nonprofit businesses.  Prior to his current position he was the CEO of CityGrid Media, an online media company that connects web and mobile publishers with local advertisers. CityGrid Media owns and operates CityGrid, a local content and advertising network, as well as leading local consumer brands such as Urbanspoon, Citysearch and InsiderPages.
 
Prior to that he served as SVP Strategic Planning at IAC as well as CEO of Evite and Interim CEO of IAC Advertising Solutions. Before joining IAC, Mr. Herratti held the position of Senior Vice President of e-Business Strategy and Development for Federated Department Stores and prior to that he held senior positions with The Boston Consulting Group and GE Capital.
  
Mr. Herratti has a B.S. in Business & Management from the University of Maryland at College Park, and an MBA from INSEAD in Fontainbleu, France.Michael D. ManganMr. Mangan has served as a Director since July 2015.

Mr. Mangan currently serves as the lead director at McCormick & Co. A veteran of a number of high profile consumer facing companies, Mr. Mangan has held various leadership roles during his tenure at Black & Decker Corp. from 2000 to 2010, including President of Worldwide Power Tools & Accessories, Chief Financial Officer and head of Investor Relations. Prior to joining Black & Decker, Mr. Mangan served as an Executive Vice President and the Chief Financial Officer of Ryland Group, Inc. Earlier in his career, he worked at General Motors and its GMAC subsidiary in various positions involving strategic and business planning, corporate finance and investments and new business activities.

Mr. Mangan has an MBA from Dartmouth College Amos Tuck School of Business and holds a Bachelor of Mechanical engineering degree from General Motors Institute.Brian P. TierneyMr. Tierney has served as a Director since February 2003. He is a nationally recognized expert in marketing and communications, an accomplished entrepreneur, and a veteran of several publicly traded corporations where he served as a senior officer. He is the Chief Executive Officer of Realtime Media LLC, a digital marketing services firm. He also serves as Chief Executive Officer of Brian Communications, a strategic communications firm. Prior to this, Mr. Tierney was Publisher of the Philadelphia Inquirer and Daily News and Chief Executive Officer of its parent company, Philadelphia Media Holdings LLC from June 2006 and August 2006, respectively, until October 2010. He previously served as Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of Tierney Holdings LLC, a private investment firm.  
From June 2004 to March 2005, he was Vice Chairman of Advanta Corp (NASDAQ: ADVNB). Prior to joining Advanta, he launched several successful advertising and public relations companies, including T2 Group and Tierney Communications, which he grew to $275 million in billings and sold to the Interpublic Group of Companies (NYSE: IPG). The firm remains one of the largest advertising agencies in the mid-Atlantic region. Mr. Tierney serves on a variety of civic, educational and charitable boards of directors.Andrea WeissAndrea M. Weiss has been a director since March 2013. Ms. Weiss has extensive specialty retail experience having served in several senior executive positions with dELiA*s Inc., The Limited, Inc., Intimate Brands, Inc., Guess, Inc., and Ann Taylor Stores, Inc. She is the founder and current President and Chief Executive Officer of Retail Consulting, Inc., a boutique consulting practice focused on product and brand development, consumer contact strategies, operational improvements, and turnarounds, and has served as its President and Chief Executive Officer since its formation in October 2002. Ms. Weiss is also the co-founder and current Managing Member of The O Alliance LLC, a new branch of Retail Consulting, Inc., which provides consulting serves with respect to omni-channel retailing.

Ms. Weiss currently also serves on several private boards as well as the boards of directors of Cracker Barrel Old Country Store, Inc., Chico’s FAS, Inc. and Pep Boys. Previously, Ms. Weiss served on the boards of directors GSI Commerce, Inc. from 2006 to 2011, Ediets.com, Inc. from 2004 to 2009 and Brookstone, Inc. from 2002 to 2005.Dawn M. ZierDawn Zier is the President and Chief Executive Officer of Nutrisystem, Inc. Ms. Zier joined Nutrisystem in November 2012 and oversees all aspects of Nutrisystem operations, including strategic partnerships, new product development, marketing and retail expansion. Since taking the helm, Dawn has led the turnaround of Nutrisystem by successfully changing the trajectory of the business and delivering customer and shareholder value with nine consecutive quarters of year-over-year growth. An engineer by education, Ms. Zier has spent most of her career in marketing, keeping her finger on the pulse of global consumers.

